org.cloudgraph.state

Class History

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudgraph.state.History

  • public class History
extends java.lang.Object
    The set of elements which are no longer effective for the current state of a graph, but are part of its "cell" history.

    Sparse columnar data stores typically preserve cell histories. For instance in HBase a {row, column, version} tuple exactly specifies a cell. And it is possible to have an unbounded number of cells where the row and column are the same but the cell address differs only in its version dimension. The graph state history is therefore preserved in order to enable features which involve re-constituting prior states of a graph.

    Since:
    0.5.2
    Author:
    Scott Cinnamond

    • Method Detail

      • getUUIDS

        public java.util.List<UUID> getUUIDS()
        Gets the value of the uuids property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the uuids property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getUUIDS().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list UUID
